# Game build output
GameBuilds/
build-*/

OloEditor/cmake_test_discovery_*.json

# Per-user Claude Code state (project-local instructions, skills, agents)
# Ignore the entire .claude/ tree except .claude/settings.json (shared project
# hooks/permissions config) and .claude/skills/ (shared, version-controlled
# project skills — e.g. run-oloengine). Each skill's own .gitignore handles
# its generated artifacts (screenshots/logs).
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/skills/
.claude/skills/**/shots/
skills-lock.json
docs/agents/

# Generated performance stress scenes (potentially 40+ MB of YAML at 200k
# instances). Only the generator is committed; regenerate on demand with
# OloEngine/tests/scripts/generate_perf_scenes.py.
OloEditor/SandboxProject/Assets/Scenes/PerfStress/

# Binary scene sidecar caches (issue #525). Derived from a scene's `.olo`/`.yaml`
# on load to skip yaml-cpp on subsequent loads; regenerated automatically and
# invalidated when the source changes. Never source-of-truth — do not commit.
*.scenebin

# Generated per-file test catalogues. Rendered from test_catalogue.json + in-file
# // OLO_TEST_LAYER markers by OloEngine/tests/scripts/generate_test_catalogue.py.
# Deliberately NOT committed: the tables change on essentially every test, and a
# tracked generated file made every parallel PR false-conflict on docs/testing.md
# (GitHub ignores the merge=union driver). Regenerate locally on demand.
docs/test-catalogue.*.md

# External assets fetched on demand by scripts/Fetch-Assets.ps1 (see scripts/assets/asset-manifest.json).
# Too large for git history, or licensed to be fetched rather than redistributed.
OloEditor/SandboxProject/Assets/Models/Stanford/
